    	<h2 class="h2">What does the Big Change fund pay for?</h2>
      <p>The fund was set up to provide homeless people with the practical items they need to build new lives off the streets, with long term sustainable support to become active, independent members of the community. This can include help with deposits, training courses, clothes for a job interview, furnishing a new flat, purchasing crockery, pots and pans and bed linen, and transport to travel to new accommodation.</p>

      <h2 class="h2">Who can apply for Big Change funding?</h2>
      <p>Anyone that is experiencing homelessness and needs to pay for items to help them get off the streets are eligiable for funding. The agencies that have signed up to the Big Change agreement can apply on your behalf, as can someone from the MCC rough sleeper team.</p>
      
