      <h2 class="h2">Who decides how the fund is spent?</h2>
      <p>For items under &pound;100, organisations signed up to the Big Change agreement can claim through an online application form.</p>
      <p>For items over &pound;, a panel reviews each application against the guidelines for the fund, and looks into whether it meets the criteria, and whether the need could be met by any other means. The panel is made up of one representative from an established organisation; two representatives from COR member organisations; one ex-rough sleeper in long-term support; and one representative from CityCo.</p>

      <h2 class="h2">Where did Big Change come from?</h2>
      <p>Big Change started when a group of grass roots organisations met up and created Coalition Of Relief (COR) in August 2015. The aim of COR was to provide a united network of relief services for the homeless of Manchester, by meeting regularly and involving as many charities services and groups as possible.</p>
      <p>From this group, Big Change emerged.  We wanted to create a collective campaign that educated people on effective ways to help, and provide fast access to funding for long term solutions.</p>

